cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual object tracking using a convolutional neural network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training of the network, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning techniques and the focus on object recognition also suggest that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of video sequences, which suggests that it may belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the network for tracking objects in real-time, which suggests that it may belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control).
